      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:3:19:1",
      "text": [
        " ثَلَاثَةٌ لَا يَقْبَلُ اللَّهُ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ لَهُمْ صَلَاةً أَحَدُهُمُ الْعَبْدُ الْآبِقُ حَتَّى يَرْجِعَ إِلَى مَوْلَاهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Khalid, and Al Husayn Bin Saeed altogether, from Al Qasim Bin Urwa, from Abdul Hameed, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Three (people) Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic will not Accept their Prayers – one of them is the absconding slave until he returns to his master’."
        ]
      }
